  <data key="d2">World Athletics Federation is an international organization that governs global athletics events, including the World Athletics Championships. It is responsible for overseeing rules and regulations pertinent to these events and ensuring their adherence by athletes during championship competitions. The federation also plays a crucial role in validating athletic records and ensuring the integrity of performance metrics across various athletic disciplines. This includes the certification of world records achieved in different sporting categories. Additionally, the World Athletics Federation oversees global athletics competitions and record validations, covering aspects from competition oversight to standardization of performance criteria. Its primary function is to maintain standards and order within international athletics, thereby contributing significantly to the organization and integrity of the sport globally.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the World Athletics Championship and validates athletic records.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees global athletics competitions like the World Athletics Championship.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees global athletics competitions like the World Athletics Championship.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the World Athletics Championship and validates athletic records.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees global athletics events such as the World Athletics Championship.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees global athletics competitions and record validations.</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
