<edge source="Noah Carter" target="World Athletics Federation">
  <data key="d7">29.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Noah Carter's participation in athletics is governed by the World Athletics Federation, an organization responsible for overseeing rules, regulations, and record validations for athletes competing in various championships. The World Athletics Federation ensures that all competitions in which Noah Carter participates adhere to established guidelines and standards set forth by the organization. This includes regulating his participation in championship events and validating any new benchmarks or record-breaking performances he achieves.

The federation plays a crucial role in confirming that records set during championship events meet necessary criteria for recognition, thereby upholding the credibility of competitive athletics. It oversees the rules and regulations governing Noah Carter's competition in international championships, ensuring fairness and integrity throughout these events. Additionally, the World Athletics Federation validates new records set by athletes like Noah Carter at major championships, recognizing their achievements according to established standards.

In summary, the World Athletics Federation is instrumental in maintaining the credibility of athletic competitions through its oversight of rules, regulations, and record validations for athletes such as Noah Carter. This includes validating records set during competitions and ensuring that all activities comply with governing principles to maintain the integrity and fairness of international championships.</data>
  <data key="d9">athlete achievement,athlete governance,athlete oversight,athlete recognition,athlete regulation,athlete supervision,athletic achievement,competition oversight,governance,governing body,oversight,record validation,regulation,validation</data>
